<br>
He had just left a meeting with his brothers and sisters and was on his way to scrounge up tales of things to be accomplished for his family to attend to. His family, AKA Silent Redemption, had become reknowned for their great and epic battles in places much to dangerous for many to travel. The latest of which was the one that caught Fizzlethorpes attention, the raid on Veeshans Peak. <br>
<br>
Fizzlethorpe knew that his apperance to the humble wood elf probably would not help their cause, at least not yet, so he traveled back to the cold stone room on the Air Plane. <br>
<br>
&quot;Lady Tunare, I believe I have found one who can assist us in our attempt,&quot; the grin spreading ever further across his partially shadowed face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then where is this great mortal who will assist us?&quot; Tunare was still very much agitated about asking mortals to help in any way with a war between fellow gods, as was everyone else. The word great rolled out of her mouth like the taste of spoiled mutton, or charred dark elf parts.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well you see Lady Tunare, the one I have found I have yet to approach. He is one of your devout followers, one who goes by the name of Ganon....&quot; He trailed the name off into silence so he could witness her reaction. &quot;I felt it best for you yourself to approach this elf yourself, for you see he might not be so cooperative should I be the one to approach him.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tunare was at ends by this time. Of course it was a priviledge , not to mention bragging rights among gods,to have one of her own be the one who was great enough to plan such an awesome strike. On the other hand she was furious that it was to be her that would have to approach a mortal to help. This was something she wasnt eager to do, regardless of what it could mean for her, for all the Council.<br>
<br>
